def gini(class1_count, class2_count):
    n = class1_count + class2_count
    return 2 * class1_count / n * class2_count / n

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
impurities = []
for class1 in range(101):
    impurities.append(gini(class1, 100 - class1))

plt.plot(np.linspace(0, 100, 101), impurities)
plt.xlabel('Instances in class1 (positive)')
plt.ylabel('Gini impurity')
plt.show()

In [ ]:
impurities = []
cutoffs = sorted(df.Temperature.unique())[:-1]
for cutoff in cutoffs:
    subset1_df = df[df.Temperature <= cutoff]
    subset2_df = df[df.Temperature > cutoff]
    subset1_gini = gini((subset1_df.label == True).sum(),
                        (subset1_df.label == False).sum())
    subset2_gini = gini((subset2_df.label == True).sum(),
                        (subset2_df.label == False).sum())
    avg_gini = (subset1_gini * len(subset1_df) +
                subset2_gini * len(subset2_df)) / len(df)
    impurities.append(avg_gini)

plt.plot(cutoffs, impurities)
plt.xlabel('Split point (temperature)')
plt.ylabel('Gini impurity')
plt.show()
